Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531208\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531208\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qdk1665702675095.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qdk1665702675095.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qdk1665702675095.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qdk1665702675095\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define a Logical Printer\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">On Windows, you can define a logical printer, which is a named collection of printer settings for a physical printer. You can define more than one logical printer for the same physical printer.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"qdk1665702675095__context_w2413ab1b5b1_w2414ab1b5_w2415ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"qdk1665702675095__topic_d65096e1_d65097e1_d65098e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qdk1665702675095__p_d65099e1_d65100e1_d65101e1\">The Uniface Setup utility must be enabled for your application. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kko1705481411881.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kko1705481411881.html\" title=\"The Setup Utility enables users to change selected initialization settings in usys.ini without restarting the application. It can be added to the system menu of an MDI Uniface desktop application.\">Setup Utility</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qdk1665702675095__p_d65102e1_d65103e1_d65104e1\">Output can be sent to the printer only if the device table specified in the print job model is appropriate to the platform and printer. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nbh1665702675570.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nbh1665702675570.html\" title=\"You must define a print job model before you can print data from Form components.\">Define a Print Job Model</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qdk1665702675095__li_d28232e1_d28233e1_d28234e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"qdk1665702675095__p_d65105e1_d65106e1_d65107e1\">In the Uniface Setup utility, click the Printer tab and click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Add</span>.\n The Printer definition dialog is displayed, with the default physical printer for your machine automatically selected.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qdk1665702675095__li_d28235e1_d28236e1_d28237e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Enter the name of the new logical printer, for example <code class=\"ph codeph\">NETWORK</code>.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qdk1665702675095__li_d28238e1_d28239e1_d28240e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">&gt;&gt;</span> to display the Windows Print Setup dialog, and set the printer properties that you want this logical printer to have, such as orientation, paper size, paper source, double-sided, and so on, and press OK.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qdk1665702675095__li_d28241e1_d28242e1_d28243e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"qdk1665702675095__p_d65108e1_d65109e1_d65110e1\">Press <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span> in the Printer definition dialog.\n The new logical printer is now visible in the Printer tab.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"qdk1665702675095__p_d65111e1_d65112e1_d65113e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"qdk1665702675095__fig_w2416ab1b5b3b7b3b1b1_w2417ab1b5b3b7b3b1_w2418ab1b5b3b7b3_w2419ab1b5b3b7_w2420ab1b5b3_w2421ab1b5_w2422ab1\">\n<img alt=\"Setup Utility with Printer tab\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/setupprinter.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"qdk1665702675095__li_d28244e1_d28245e1_d28246e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span> in the Printer tab to save the definition in the Registry and add the logical printer to the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LogPrinter</span> setting in <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span>.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hvd1665702670692.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>LogPrinter</a><p>Specifies one or more logical printers for the application. Windows only.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/guw1665702607063.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Print Job Models</a><p>A print job model is a named collection of printer attributes that determine how and where Uniface forms or reports are printed, including details of the device type, margins, and so on. A print job model must be available before you can print.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kko1705481411881.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Setup Utility</a><p>The Setup Utility enables users to change selected initialization settings in usys.ini without restarting the application. It can be added to the system menu of an MDI Uniface desktop application.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531208\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531208\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define a Logical Printer Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define a Logical Printer On Windows, you can define a logical printer, which is a named collection of printer settings for a physical printer. You can define more than one logical printer for the same physical printer. The Uniface Setup utility must be enabled for your application. For more information, see Setup Utility . Output can be sent to the printer only if the device table specified in the print job model is appropriate to the platform and printer. For more information, see Define a Print Job Model . In the Uniface Setup utility, click the Printer tab and click Add . The Printer definition dialog is displayed, with the default physical printer for your machine automatically selected. Enter the name of the new logical printer, for example NETWORK . Click >> to display the Windows Print Setup dialog, and set the printer properties that you want this logical printer to have, such as orientation, paper size, paper source, double-sided, and so on, and press OK. Press OK in the Printer definition dialog. The new logical printer is now visible in the Printer tab. Click OK in the Printer tab to save the definition in the Registry and add the logical printer to the LogPrinter setting in usys.ini . Related Links LogPrinter Specifies one or more logical printers for the application. Windows only. Print Job Models A print job model is a named collection of printer attributes that determine how and where Uniface forms or reports are printed, including details of the device type, margins, and so on. A print job model must be available before you can print. Setup Utility The Setup Utility enables users to change selected initialization settings in usys.ini without restarting the application. It can be added to the system menu of an MDI Uniface desktop application. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}